HEADWORD: Kilolitre
<hw>Kil"o*li`tre</hw>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>kilolitre</ets>. See
<er>Kilogram</er>, and <er>Liter</er>.]</ety> <def>A measure of capacity
equal to a cubic meter, or a thousand liters. It is equivalent to 35.315
cubic feet, and to 220.04 imperial gallons, or 264.18 American gallons
of 321 cubic inches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

